# jitsudo License

This repository contains code under two different licenses, applied to
different components. Please read carefully before using or contributing.

## CLI, Provider SDK, and OPA Policy Libraries — Apache License 2.0

The following components are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0:

- `cmd/jitsudo/` — CLI binary entrypoint
- `internal/cli/` — CLI command implementations
- `internal/providers/` — Provider interface and all cloud provider adapters
- `pkg/` — Public Go packages (client library, shared types)
- All Rego policy files under `policies/`

You may use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell
copies of these components freely. See `LICENSE-APACHE` for the full text.

## Control Plane Server — Elastic License 2.0 (ELv2)

The following components are licensed under the Elastic License 2.0:

- `cmd/jitsudod/` — Control plane daemon entrypoint
- `internal/server/` — Control plane implementation (API handlers, auth,
  policy engine, workflow, audit log, notifications)

The key restriction of ELv2: **you may not provide the software to third
parties as a hosted or managed service** where the service provides users
with access to any substantial set of the features or functionality of the
software.

Self-hosted deployment for your own organization's use is unrestricted.
See `LICENSE-ELV2` for the full text.

## What This Means in Practice

| Use case | Permitted? |
|----------|-----------|
| An SRE downloading and self-hosting jitsudo for their team | Yes |
| A company running jitsudo internally across their entire org | Yes |
| A startup building their platform security on top of jitsudo | Yes |
| A consulting firm deploying jitsudo for a client's internal use | Yes |
| A cloud provider offering "Managed jitsudo" as a billable service | No |
| A SaaS company offering jitsudo-as-a-service to multiple customers | No |

## Questions?

If you have questions about licensing, open an issue or contact the maintainers
via the security contact in `SECURITY.md`.
